// docs/spec/en/05-unions-and-packed-layout.md §9.4(6): the same
// incompleteness rule applies "including" but not limited to a bare
// top-level `sizeof(Self)` -- it governs any required constant evaluation
// that would need the enclosing type's size, however deeply the
// self-reference is nested inside a larger constant-expression. Here the
// self-reference is one operand of an arithmetic combination rather than
// the whole bound, confirming the rejection is not merely a special case
// for a bare `sizeof(Self)` token.
struct SelfArith {
    char buf[sizeof(SelfArith) + 4]; // ill-formed: SelfArith is incomplete here too
};

int main() {
    SelfArith s{};
    return 0;
}
